            <section id="overview" class="content-section active bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-700 mb-4">Overview of TAQA Distribution and Network</h2>
                <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">This section provides an introduction to TAQA Distribution, formed from the merger of ADDC and AADC, and its role in Abu Dhabi's power distribution. It highlights the importance of the 11kV and 33kV cable networks for reliable electricity supply across residential, commercial, and industrial sectors. You'll find information on network characteristics and TAQA's strategic objectives, including its commitment to a smart, sustainable, and digitally integrated network.</p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-2">TAQA Distribution Context</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Abu Dhabi National Energy Company (TAQA) is an integrated utility group. The distribution arm, TAQA Distribution, unified ADDC and AADC from January 2025, serving over 1,080,000 service points.</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">The merger aims for operational synergies, harmonized standards, and enhanced customer service across Abu Dhabi.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-2">Network Characteristics (11kV & 33kV)</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">The distribution system operates at 33kV and lower. Standardized connection arrangements (ER-11) exist for 11kV (Category B) and 33kV (Category D) connections.</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Security of Supply Standard (ER-04) dictates performance, like restoration times (e.g., 11kV ring feeder: 50% demand in 20 mins, full in 2 hours with remote/auto switching).</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Future network development will support UAE's Net Zero by 2050, integrating renewables and evolving into an intelligent grid.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                 <div class="mt-6">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3 text-center">Key Network Figures</h3>
