            <section id="faults" class="content-section bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-700 mb-4">Common Cable Faults</h2>
                <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">Explore common faults affecting 11kV and 33kV underground distribution cables. This section covers fault classifications (electrical, insulation, mechanical, environmental, accessory failures), analyzes specific fault types, and discusses contributing factors. An interactive display, based on Table 2 of the source report, helps you understand causes and consequences. A chart illustrates the typical distribution of fault types.</p>
                
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3">Fault Classification Highlights</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4 space-y-1">
                    <li><strong>Electrical Faults:</strong> Short circuits (L-G, L-L, L-L-L) and open circuits. Single Line-to-Ground (L-G) are most common (60-80%).</li>
                    <li><strong>Insulation Degradation:</strong> Partial Discharge (PD), Electrical Treeing (TAQA specifies "tree-retardant" XLPE), Water Treeing, Thermal Degradation.</li>
                    <li><strong>Mechanical Damage:</strong> Often by third-party excavation; also installation damage or vibration.</li>
                    <li><strong>Environmental Factors:</strong> Moisture ingress, corrosion (TAQA specifies sulphide-resistant outer sheath).</li>
                    <li><strong>Accessory Failures:</strong> Joints and terminations are critical points; PILC-XLPE transition joints are notably vulnerable.</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3">Common Faults Details</h3>
                <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">Click on each fault category to expand and see details.</p>
                <div id="cableFaultsTable" class="space-y-2"></div>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 my-6 text-center">Typical MV Cable Fault Type Distribution</h3>
