            <section id="standards" class="content-section bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-700 mb-4">Applicable Standards & Compliance</h2>
                <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">The design, manufacture, testing, and operation of 11kV and 33kV cable systems are governed by a hierarchy of standards. This section provides an overview of key international standards (IEC, BS), regional (GCC), and local TAQA/ADDC/AADC specifications and Engineering Recommendations that ensure safety, reliability, and interoperability. TAQA's local specifications take precedence in case of any conflict.</p>
                
                <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="accordion-item border border-gray-200 rounded">
                        <button class="accordion-header w-full text-left p-3 bg-sky-50 hover:bg-sky-100 rounded-t font-medium">International Standards <span class="float-right">‚ñº</span></button>
                        <div class="accordion-content p-3 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-600">
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                                <li><strong>IEC 60502-2:</strong> Power cables with extruded insulation (6kV to 30kV). Core standard for XLPE cables.</li>
                                <li><strong>IEC 60228:</strong> Conductors of insulated cables.</li>
                                <li><strong>IEC 60287 series:</strong> Calculation of current rating.</li>
                                <li><strong>BS 6622:</strong> Armoured thermosetting insulated cables (3.8/6.6kV to 19/33kV).</li>
                                <li><strong>BS 7870 series:</strong> LV and MV distribution cables (incl. LSZH).</li>
                                <li><strong>BS 7835:</strong> Armoured thermosetting insulated cables with low smoke/corrosive gas emission.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item border border-gray-200 rounded">
                        <button class="accordion-header w-full text-left p-3 bg-sky-50 hover:bg-sky-100 rounded-t font-medium">TAQA/ADDC/AADC Specifications & Engineering Recommendations (ERs) <span class="float-right">‚ñº</span></button>
                        <div class="accordion-content p-3 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-600">
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                                <li><strong>S-CAB-UMV-3CAL_00.DOCX:</strong> TAQA/ADDC/AADC standard for 11, 22 & 33KV XLPE-Insulated Three-Core Underground Cables with Aluminium Conductors. This is the primary local specification.</li>
                                <li><strong>ER-04:</strong> Security of Supply Standard. Defines reliability criteria and restoration times.</li>
                                <li><strong>ER-08:</strong> Earthing System Design & Installation. Critical for safety and fault current management.</li>
                                <li><strong>ER-11:</strong> Standard Connection Arrangements for User Systems. Defines interface requirements.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                     <div class="accordion-item border border-gray-200 rounded">
                        <button class="accordion-header w-full text-left p-3 bg-sky-50 hover:bg-sky-100 rounded-t font-medium">Regional (GCC) Standards <span class="float-right">‚ñº</span></button>
                        <div class="accordion-content p-3 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-600">
                             <p>The GCC Standardization Organization (GSO) also develops relevant standards (e.g., GSO EN 45510-2-8:2021 for procurement of LV/MV power cables).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

