            <section id="recommendations" class="content-section bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-700 mb-4">Recommendations & Future Outlook</h2>
                <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">This section summarizes key recommendations for enhancing the reliability, safety, and operational efficiency of TAQA Distribution's 11kV and 33kV cable networks. It also touches upon the future outlook for power distribution, considering smart grid integration and evolving technologies.</p>
                
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-2">Key Recommendations</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Strict Adherence to Specifications:</strong> Follow TAQA's latest standards (e.g., S-CAB-UMV-3CAL_00.DOCX) and use approved vendors. Consider LSZH cables for high fire-risk areas.</li>
                    <li><strong>Proactive Fault Management:</strong> Implement systematic diagnostic testing (VLF, Tan Delta, PD). Develop strategies for managing legacy PILC cables and transition joints. Maintain detailed fault records.</li>
                    <li><strong>Best Practices for Equipment & Training:</strong> Use modern, calibrated fault location equipment. Invest in comprehensive training for jointers and fault teams. Standardize on approved accessories and ensure meticulous installation.</li>
                    <li><strong>Periodic Review of Standards:</strong> Regularly update ER-04, ER-08, etc., to align with network growth and technological advancements.</li>
                    <li><strong>Leverage TAQA Unification:</strong> Establish a single, best-practice framework for cable system management post-merger.</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Analytics:</strong> Invest in analytics for fault/diagnostic data to predict at-risk segments and optimize maintenance.</li>
                    <li><strong>Manufacturer Collaboration:</strong> Foster R&D partnerships for products suited to the harsh Middle Eastern environment.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-2">Future Outlook</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Smart Grid Integration:</strong> Cables with embedded sensing, enhanced communication.</li>
                    <li><strong>Distributed Renewables:</strong> Cables managing bi-directional power flows and dynamic loads.</li>
                    <li><strong>Material Science Advancements:</strong> Improved thermal performance, environmental resilience, smaller footprints.</li>
                    <li><strong>Continuous Improvement:</strong> Learn from internal data, benchmark internationally, integrate new technologies.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
